text: Fiona Campbell (12 May 1929 - 8 September 2005) was a British alpine skier. She competed in two events at the 1952 Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:2005 deaths Category:British female alpine skiers Category:Olympic alpine skiers of Great Britain Category:Alpine skiers at the 1952 Winter Olympics Category:People from Hamilton, Bermuda
